Prefer pickup? No problem. Know the fees upfront and track orders from Grubhub delivery partners in real time—the only surprise is just how easy takeout can be. ORDER FROM THOUSANDS OF RESTAURANTS With Grubhub, you can order takeout from your favorite local restaurants and everyone’s favorite chains. There are so many good eats out there, but you obviously deserve the best. Grubhub makes it easier to choose your next meal with restaurant ratings and reviews. French fries, pizza, burritos, burgers, sushi, donuts—it’s all here, whenever a craving strikes. GET GROCERIES DELIVERED TOO Think beyond your breakfast, lunch, and dinner orders. Grubhub offers the ultimate convenience with grocery delivery, in addition to restaurant takeout. Order milk, bread, snacks, and frozen foods, as well as household essentials like paper towels and laundry detergent, from local convenience stores. EXPECT TO SEE THE FEES UPFRONT Grubhub gives it to you straight. See the delivery fee upfront, before you start crafting the perfect food order. Pay your way with credit cards, Grubhub gift cards, or Venmo. SKIP DELIVERY FEES The key is Grubhub+. Sign up for unlimited $0 delivery fees on eligible orders, and enjoy exclusive offers and rewards as a Grubhub+ member.* Try Grubhub+ free for 30 days, then level up for just $9.99/month. The truth is, food tastes even better when you spend less on delivery. See details below. TRACK DELIVERY IN REAL TIME Grubhub puts your delivery on the map. Track eligible orders in real time, from the restaurant to your front door, and know the moment your bacon-egg-and-cheese arrives. Every delivery is a special delivery with Grubhub. COUNT ON THE GRUBHUB GUARANTEE Get your food delivered on time and at the lowest price. Guaranteed, or we’ll make it right. See details: grubhub.com/guarantee YOU DO YOU AND GRUBHUB DELIVERS Grubhub serves up a personalized app experience, so you can reorder that feast you’re still thinking about from two months ago. Order sauce on the side, go for extra pickles, lose the onions—Grubhub gets you. Are you a regular? Get rewarded when you come back for more at the same restaurants. You can also plan ahead by pre-ordering food for pickup or delivery. ORDER FROM NATIONAL RESTAURANTS Sometimes you need a sure thing, and that’s why Grubhub partners with national restaurants to offer the takeout food you know and love. Get delivery from Applebee’s, Arby’s, Buffalo Wild Wings, Burger King, Chick-fil-A, Chipotle, Denny’s, Dunkin’, Five Guys, IHOP, McDonald’s, KFC, Panda Express, Panera, Papa John’s, Popeyes, Shake Shack, Subway, Taco Bell, Wendy’s, White Castle, and more. GET SUPPORT WHEN YOU NEED IT Burning questions? Delivery crisis? Grubhub customer support is here for you 24/7. *$0 delivery fees only apply to eligible delivery orders from Grubhub+ merchants that meet the subtotal minimum (before tax, tip, and fees) on the applicable menu page or otherwise indicated on the Grubhub platform. Grubhub+ is an automatically renewing membership service requiring recurring payments. After your free trial ends, your free trial will convert to a paid Grubhub+ membership and Grubhub will automatically charge you each month at the then-current rate (currently $9.99) plus tax until you cancel. Top brand and local heroes Order from big brands like McDonald's, Burger King, KFC, Pizza Hut, Domino’s, Wagamama, Starbucks, Greggs, Costa Coffee and even more local favourites. apps.description: Yango is an easy-to-use app for getting around the city Fill your life with movement. Get the whole city in your hands, ride wherever you want, and enjoy comfort at an affordable price. With Yango, everything is possible! Choose the right service class for you Reach your destination at the right level of comfort and price for you. Choose from several service classes. Economy is awesome for when you need a ride fast. Comfort lets you sit back and just enjoy the ride. And The Fastest is the best in case when the service class doesn’t matter and you just need the closest ride available! Ride safely Safety is our top priority. You’ll see who’s coming to pick you up and in which car right in the app. You’ll see info about the driver, such as their name and rating, and will be able to share your route with whomever you like so they know where you are. Smart destinations Yango will suggest destinations for your rides based on your ride history, like first offering ‘home’ as a destination because it’s your most common request on weekday evenings. Ride the smart way! Multiple destinations, one route Yango makes everyday life super easy. Like picking the kids up from school, dropping a friend off at a market, and doing some quick shopping on the way. Just add a new stop in the app, and Yango will recalculate a new route for the driver. Request rides for close ones Show you care by requesting rides for friends and relatives. Get your mother to a doctor’s appointment, book a ride to pick up your special someone, or get each of your friends a ride home after a night out. You can request up to 3 cars at once. Refer friends and get discounts Invite friends to try Yango and save together. Share your personal promo code, get a discount on your next ride and grant your friend with an extra discount on their first ride. It’s as easy as that. Meet Delivery - it's like a taxi service, but for your packages We've also built in a fast delivery service into Yango - use Delivery to quickly send personal packages or even business orders by courier anywhere in the city. Delivery is suitable for any item that can be transported by scooter or car. An international service Yango is a ride-hailing, mobility, and delivery aggregator service that operates in more than 20 countries around the world, including Ghana, Cote d'Ivoire, Cameroon, Senegal and Zambia. Yango is an informational service and not a transportation or taxi services provider. Transportation services are provided by third parties. The size and duration of the discount for the first rides requested via the Yango app vary depending on the country and city. Open the app for specific details. apps.title: maxim: order a taxi & delivery
apps.description: The best way to appreciate the convenience of our app is to download it and start using it to order a taxi and other transport. Rates vary. Ride to the railway station, airport, or another city. Pay by cash or card. Enjoy discounts and promo codes. Since 2003, we’ve been developing innovative taxi ordering technologies, making our service more modern, affordable, and safe. Our service is helping millions of people save money as they commute and travel. Price If you need a cheap taxi every day, choose our Economy rate. If you value comfort, opt for the Comfort rate. We also have minivans, buses, and trucks. You can order a delivery of food, household cleaning products and other goods or medicine from shops and drugstores. You can see your ride price before tapping the Order button, which is useful for planning your budget. Don’t worry about traffic – you only pay extra for additional services that were not specified in the order. Enjoy the convenience of paying for rides with cash and a credit card. You can use a personal account that you refill whenever necessary for corporate or family rides. It’s easy to get discounted rides if you use a promo code or you are one of our regular clients. Order You can order a ride by filling in the From and To address fields or using a city map. You can also use your smartphone’s or tablet’s location services. A scheduled order helps you plan your rides for a convenient time. You can provide special requests for your ride to arrange any necessary additional services: specify information about children, pets, or luggage; or add another phone number to order a taxi for someone else from your phone. A driver can buy goods, medicine or groceries, and deliver them to your place. Launch our app on Wear OS smart watch to track your ride status. View a map to see available cars and your driver’s movement as he or she approaches your location. You can share your location while you are en route. This is an important feature for parents who want to know their children are safe. Leaving a ride rating affects the driver’s rating and helps us improve our service. apps.description: If you are looking for an app to track deliveries on iPhone, iPad, Mac or Apple Watch - Parcel is the best choice for you. With this application you can promptly access tracking information for 300 delivery services, including UPS, USPS, FedEx, DHL, TNT, LaserShip, Aramex, OnTrac, China Post, Amazon Logistics and many other carriers. Full list of supported carriers is available at: https://parcel.app With our unique carrier recognition function, adding a new delivery is just a matter of seconds. Sometimes you won't even need to enter a tracking number, you can use a barcode scanner which is available right in the app. Amazon integration in Parcel allows you to get your packages added automatically from your Amazon account. Once an order is shipped, it will appear in Parcel. This is done in a secure and privacy-friendly way with your credentials never leaving the device. You can also locate your delivery on the map or manage your deliveries using Web Access (web.parcelapp.net) - easy and simple. Parcel has a native macOS app available for free in the Mac App Store. Parcel utilizes the power of iOS to provide you the best possible user experience. You can use its widgets to see your upcoming deliveries and the share extension to add a new delivery directly from any other app. Push notifications provided by Parcel are more convenient than from any other app. They are being sent only from 8am to 10 pm according to your timezone, so you will not be bothered at night (however, you can disable this option in the settings). Some features, such as push notifications and tracking more than 3 deliveries are limited to premium subscribers. Current price for the premium subscription is $4.99 per year, and may vary from country to country. Parcel's privacy policy, as well as subscription terms are available at https://parcel.app/privacy-with-terms.html.
